docs/adrs/ADR-009-audit-logging.md:7:The PRD requires a "Hard Gate" for audit log completeness (100% of protocol mutations, dose logs, and order events). This is necessary for security, system integrity, and potentially future regulatory compliance.
docs/adrs/ADR-009-audit-logging.md:10:We will implement a system-wide `audit_events` table in PostgreSQL to store immutable records of all sensitive state changes.
docs/adrs/ADR-009-audit-logging.md:13:- **Application Logs (Stdout)**: Easier to implement but ephemeral and harder to query for user-facing audit trails.
docs/adrs/ADR-009-audit-logging.md:15:- **Temporal / Event Sourcing**: Provides a complete audit trail but adds significant architectural complexity.
docs/adrs/ADR-009-audit-logging.md:19:- **Costs**: Database storage growth (mitigated by 90-day rolling purge); additional latency on writes to record the audit event.
docs/domain-models/ordering.md:7:- **Payment Confirmation**: The explicit step where a user verifies the destination wallet and amount.
docs/domain-models/ordering.md:17:  - `status`: enum (Draft, Sent, Confirmed, PaymentSent, Received, Cancelled, Stale)
docs/domain-models/ordering.md:18:  - `paymentConfirmation`: PaymentConfirmation (Value Object, optional)
docs/domain-models/ordering.md:24:### PaymentConfirmation
docs/domain-models/ordering.md:37:  - `status` cannot transition to `PaymentSent` without a completed `paymentConfirmation`.
docs/domain-models/ordering.md:42:- `PaymentAcknowledged`: User completes the safety gate verification.
docs/adrs/index.md:18:| ADR-012 | Use Railway Cron for Scheduled Jobs | Accepted | 2026-05-20 |
docs/adrs/ADR-002-postgresql-prisma.md:15:- **SQLite (local-first)**: Simplifies some things but complicates multi-user data synchronization and server-side Telegram session management.
docs/adrs/ADR-015-module-isolation.md:14:4. **Feature Flag**: A `DISABLE_ORDERING` environment variable will completely hide the module from the UI and block API routes.

